Swagger is a tool used to:
Document REST APIs 
Test APIs in browser 
Generate API information automatically 
Provide interactive API UI 
Nowadays, Swagger is commonly implemented using:
OpenAPI 
Swagger UI
Swagger UI Example URL
After configuration:
http://localhost:8080/swagger-ui/index.html




Consider the project:

MonicaCDAC/SBPrj3_JPA



Open Pom.xml:
Add Dependency:

<dependency>
    <groupId>org.springdoc</groupId>
    <artifactId>springdoc-openapi-starter-webmvc-ui</artifactId>
    <version>2.5.0</version>
</dependency>




Run Application:
Mvn clean
mvn install
mvn spring-boot:run









